FBIS3-39325 "drweu032aa_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-032 Document Type:Daily Report 16 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS IAEA, DPRK Reach Accord on Nuclear Inspections AU1502165094 Paris AFP in English 1638 GMT 15 Feb 94 AU1502165094 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Vienna, Feb 15 (AFP) -- North Korea and the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) reached agreement here Tuesday [15 February] on resuming inspections of Pyongyang's nuclear facilities, the agency's spokesman said. David Kyd said that the two sides had reached an accord on inspecting seven identified sites and that an IAEA mission of two to three weeks' duration would enter North Korea as soon as visa formalities had been dealt with. Kyd said Pyongyang had accepted all IAEA demands concerning the nature of the inspections, which the IAEA in anxious to carry out amid growing suspicions that Pyongyang has an active nuclear weapons programme.
